ordinated through Gyne ONC.'),(1065,705168100,2,'urgently for his lower back pain and will arrange Pall RT as an outpatient to his CHEST if needed. Overall his treatment plan will be largely paliative. He is at high risk of Social compromize and has NO social supports. It is indeterminate if his bone mets are from prostate CA vs Esophgeal Ca - but his Rising PSA 500 suggests that these could be from his prostate. Further hormonal therapy may be advised but his life expectancy from the Esophagus is limited < 1 year.'),(1066,964491710,2,'I have booked Sim - Consult with Dr Monzon in 2 weeks.'),(1067,729266610,2,'Her CP score has clinically improved to B7. After a very careful discussion she would like to proceed. I have Cancelled the removal fo the Catheter and ro-ordred home care'),(1068,755619851,2,'urgently. Treatment to proceed within 1 week. She will call us tomorrow when she is well enough to lay flat for Sim.,'),(1069,398920330,7,'we have arragned FU with Dr Dowden'),(1070,136448310,5,'Re-excision shows residual disease but negative margins. We discussed pros cons of further RT vs observation. She favors observation. She may continue that with Dr Datta. Re-referral to the cancer center if there are any new masses'),(1071,509461920,2,'Patient is away Oct to Apr - we will cordiante imaging around this for when he returns. SBRT wil be done prior. He wants to be off of chemo and will arrange FU and re-refer if there is progression.'),(1072,722876310,2,'Patient is away aug 8-16 we will work around these dates for Sim and biopsy'),(1073,292361021,9,'We will reserve Radiation for stable localized disease after 1st line therapy. Ill book him back with a phone call in 3-4 months to see how he has done with chemo. I will let Dr Tam coordinate imaging.'),(1074,534961090,2,NULL),(1075,256109420,9,'for RT at this time. Patient look very poor we tried to discuss end of life but the family wanted to remain hopeful and did not want to discuss this. I am worried that he is dete