ninging the IPI - we suggested that this could be addressed by Dr Heng in the future. I will arrange fu in 3-4 mo - but I will leave all further FU / Scans wth Dr Heng'),(1085,157647131,9,'Patient is decining rapidly at home. The family wishes a home passing and pall HC are well involved. He is imminently about to pass and there would be little role for RT at this time.'),(1086,854360210,2,'HOLD chemo after Aug 16 he can restart 4 weeks post RT. I have booked imaging 3 mo post RT. He should keep his PT scan for brain he should continue seeing Dr Loewen for his CNS disease (subtle recent changes).  I will treat the lungs squentially with 3 -6 mo gap depending on repsonse and toxicity.'),(1087,106098300,5,'HGB s being monitored - every 2 weeks stable around 90. he tolerated RT well no side effects. I called the nursing team at his care facilities and reviewed his daily care pattern particularly around the diaper and bowel movements they are watching for bleeding, and have not noted any unusual patterns.'),(1088,208305900,9,'of radiation at this time due to the presence of lung metastasis. Although all of these sites are amenable to SBRT our current clinical protocl requries that the patient be evaluated for systemic therapy first and SBRT be reserved for refractory / residual disease after standard of care therapy. RTOG trial is now closed for accrual and we are still awaiting opening of COMET 3 - to which she may be technically eligible. Proceeding with systemic therapy will be favoured. She also will not be able to participate in clinical trials due to language barrier. She has a consultation with Dr Tam. I will await his consultation. She may be re-referred in the future if SBRT is needed for oligometastatic disease.   I would highly recommend a Mandarin or cantonese translator - the patient require extensive explanation of even very basic things. She was unaware that she had a recurrence, how scans are done or why, she needed to be clarified that this is NOT breast cancer and why that her mammogram which was normal is not a clear bill of health. Very basic principles of cancer therapy and knoweldge needed explanation.'),(1089,988562800,9,'given the prior radiaton and very likely this being a radiation induced malignancy - it is difficut to justify adding radation either conventional or SBRT to the patient at this time. The adjuvant role of Chemo radiation is already poorly supported by the evidence and certainly the risk in the retreat scenario is much higher. There is NO role of adjuvant SBRT in the absense of measurable mass or recurrence - and even if there were a visible localized recurrence - to do so in the proximity of previously irradiated duodenum and other GI structures would be needed to be calculated very carefully if at all.  I spoke to Dr Tam about potential radiation recall and will investigate if there are any therapy interventions. I cautioned proceeding with further chemo until his CT scan and labs were more normal.'),(1090,874692900,2,'I have arranged Blood transfusion, and urgent RT. We agree that MO consut is not needed.'),(1091,691975600,8,'. I have Booked a FU in 2 weeks. He cannot afford to travel or come to calgary for treatment. We will ask Social services to faciliate travel fr RT Sim and 5# of treatment daily. He would need hostel. IF he cannot be funded he would not be able to come for treatment. He also remans undecided if he wants treatment at all. And may be more inclined to chemo which can be given locally although not as effective. We will call him back in 2 weeks with his decision.'),(1092,589071920,5,'no clinical evidence of recurrence. She continues to have significant sexual issues with Pain on intercourse and initial insertion she is using the vaginal dilator infrequently and is sexually active 1-2 / week. We have adviesed discussion with my nurse for sexual eduation. OASIS referral, She also has pelvic floor issues and bladder emptying issues for which she is seeing Urologist cysto pending.'),(1093,389186470,5,'She has no new symptoms, and has slight ongoing progression of the lung mets. The patient is very clear that she doesnt want any chemo at this time. There is no role for RT. I advise that we follow her clinically moving forward and can intervene for new symptoms. I will transfer her fu to Dr Pinilla and she can be re-referred if she develops symptoms.'),(1094,999183811,2,'I have booked sim.'),(1095,404306180,2,'I will arrange RT to be given concurrently with Chemo. I would like to see how he tolerates Etoposide so we will likely be doing treatment after cycle 3. There is NO need to coordinate RT or chemo.'),(1096,817114531,2,'We had an extesive discussion about the patients values. He would like to spend his remaining time being able to take care of his wife who is in a nursing home. He doesnt wish to risk his current QOL for the potential of cure. I had very clear sense of his values and wishes for QOL over cure.'),(1097,485325500,9,'. We will see her back in a few months with CT results we will consider SBRT vs Surgery or clincal trials.'),(1098,728084900,5,NULL),(1099,454079700,2,'I will arrange RT to the whole brain and Lung within the next 2 weeks she can start her chemo afterwards.'),(1100,763838820,2,NULL),(1101,268699220,2,'I emailed him all the documents prescriptions and consent.'),(1102,619493600,8,'Patient is in town from sept 8-10 for testing. We will arrange simulation at that time. I will book him back to see me sept 15. to finalize treatment plan.'),(1103,373432611,2,'Please hold Chemo - may restart in 2 weeks after Radiation.'),(1104,331250920,2,'I have booked scan for the bone and L shoulder which was incompletely visualized on CT. We will treat this if there is evidence of cancer.'),(1105,145786720,8,'He seemed quite surprised by the discussion and extent of disease. He seemed very reluctant to have chemo side effects. I emphasized that I believe that the patient will benefit from CHEMO FIRST and then offering local ther